bug.author: GoldenSpark
bug.summary: DisChnPrunedLearner with resnet18 on ImageNet can't converge in local mode

comments.comment: When I run the demo in tutorial with command ./scripts/run_local.sh nets/resnet_at_ilsvrc12_run.py --learner dis-chn-pruned. The log shows info with two lines over and over again just like this: INFO:tensorflow : layer <denchmark-link:https://github.com/Tencent/PocketFlow/issues/18>#18</denchmark-link> ： prune_ratio=0.5879 INFO:tensorflow: adding channel #0 to the non-pruned set INFO:tensorflow : layer <denchmark-link:https://github.com/Tencent/PocketFlow/issues/18>#18</denchmark-link> ： prune_ratio=0.5879 INFO:tensorflow: adding channel #0 to the non-pruned set ... This situation has been lasting for several hours . I think it may be abnormal. Please help me check it . Thanks!

<denchmark-link:https://github.com/GoldenSpark>@GoldenSpark</denchmark-link>
Could you please post the full log, especially the part before "INFO:tensorflow : layer #...： prune_ratio = ..."?
